{
  "number": 729,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/729",
  "title": "search-box is not updated when input has focus and back button pressed",
  "body": "![bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/11691037/92255d1c-9e99-11e5-83e0-b088396feb22.gif)\n\nThis is not a new bug since 1.0.0, it was already here. I guess it depends on the browser/OS but for me clicking on back button does not focus out the input. Thus it is not updated.\n\nI think we need to have a way to know when the query was updated from the outside rather than from the input itself.\n\nRight now we use [helper.on('change')](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/fix/update-search-box-on-helper-state/src/widgets/search-box/search-box.js#L163-L166) and then see if the input is focused.\n\nBut there are cases where the input is focused and the query might change still:\n- custom widget modifying the query based on a timer for example (weird but ok)\n- back button while the input is focused and stay focused\n- back navigation shortcut while focused (fails)\n\nI wonder how could we change the searchbox so that we really update it and distinguish when the event comes from the outside.\n\nI feel this is something REACT solved for instance :D\n",
